Selenium 3.1.0 onwards needs guava 21 for the wait.until method.
Try adding this to your pom, preferable near the top in case another dependency is importing and older version of guava:
      
    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;com.google.guava&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;guava&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;21.0&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

I think your problem is in this line of code 

    WebElement element=wait.until(ExpectedConditions.visibilityOfElementLocated(By.id(&quot;dnn_dnnUser_enhancedRegisterLink&quot;)));


As Wait.until is used to tell your web driver to wait until a certain action to occur which is visibility of The element located by ID = &quot;dnn_dnnUser_enhancedRegisterLink&quot; in your case 
but this method Doesn&#39;t return a web element object so you can&#39;t use it to define a web element 

Instead you just need to write :

    wait.until(ExpectedConditions.visibilityOfElementLocated(By.id(&quot;dnn_dnnUser_enhancedRegisterLink&quot;)));

